The CCTV footage of the night Tshegofatso Pule was killed may be faulty, say Ntuthuko Shoba's lawyers. Shoba's lawyers had previously submitted the footage as evidence. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The CCTV footage of the night Tshegofatso Pule was killed may be faulty, say Ntuthuko Shoba's lawyers. Shoba's lawyers had previously submitted the footage as evidence. WATCH: Case against Ntuthuko Shoba reopened It shows that Shoba was outside for three minutes with Pule when she was collected by her killer, who she thought was an Uber driver. Pule was shot and found hanging from a tree in June 2020. READ: Shoba cross-examination begins Her killer Muzikayise Malephane claims Shoba wanted her dead to hide her pregnancy from his wife. Judgment is expected on 25 March. * eNCA's Slindelo Masikane reports.